      <intermediateExchange id="a371f959-ec9d-5272-a522-319632a8da82" unitId="2f4daad7-5331-4f14-930c-d8bca924557d" amount="0.0514" intermediateExchangeId="cfbce515-3f54-4411-ad9d-3d26b7faa15a" activityLinkId="3246f83e-83a9-5eb7-8333-1be9e0fa4858">
        <name xml:lang="en">transport, freight, lorry, unspecified</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">metric ton*km</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Transport distance based on eurostat transport statistics for road freight transport. The transport data was extracted from the database leaf 'Annual road freight transport, by type of goods and type of transport (1 000 t, Mio Tkm), from 2008 onwards (road_go_ta_tg)' (http://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/data/database) on the 2018-06-01. The transport distance was calculated based on the total mass of goods transported and total payload-distance for the NST 2007 category 'GT08 - Chemicals, chemical products, and man-made fibers; rubber and plastic products ; nuclear fuel' in the year 2016 for all countries for which data was available. The average distance of road transport for goods in this category in 2016 was 216 km. The fraction of goods transported by road (in terms of mass) relative to the total mass of goods transported by road, rail and inland waterways was 79% in 2016. Therefore, the average distance that goods travelled by road in 2016 was 171 km. This value is assumed to be representative for Europe.
Furthermore, for this specific product, the transport distance was reduced by 70% as it is considered not to be transported over long distances. It is also assumed not to be transported by ship.</comment>
        <uncertainty>
          <lognormal meanValue="0.0514" mu="-2.9681171065210177" variance="0.12" varianceWithPedigreeUncertainty="0.17200000000000001"/>
          <pedigreeMatrix reliability="3" completeness="5" temporalCorrelation="3" geographicalCorrelation="1" furtherTechnologyCorrelation="4"/>
        </uncertainty>
